This paper discusses the use of mobile broadband communications in disaster and emergency scenarios, which falls under the category of networked systems and technologies. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture). The paper also discusses the allocation of spectrum resources and the impact on commercial operators, which could fall under the categories of cs.CR (Cryptography and Security) and cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing). The paper also mentions the use of virtualization for wireless networks, which could fall under the category of cs.MM (Multimedia). Finally, the paper discusses the delivery of services to users, which could fall under the category of cs.IT (Information Theory).
